description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Shifts available at all our main sites:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lincoln County Hospital, Lincoln&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pilgrim Hospital, Boston&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grantham &amp; District Hospital, Grantham&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;County Hospital, Louth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust (ULHT) is actively seeking to recruit Registered Nurses to join their bank team with shifts across all areas, including Medicine, Surgery, Orthopaedics, A&amp;E, Theatres, Elderly Care, Critical Care, Emergency Admissions and Paediatrics. Vacancies are available on all our sites: Lincoln County Hospital, Boston Pilgrim Hospital, Grantham District Hospital and County Hospital Louth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for nurses who can act as an advocate for patients and carers, who can ensure that their needs are met whilst liaising with other members of the multi-disciplinary team and who can take an active role in facilitating a safe and timely discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be delivering a high standard of patient care using flexible, innovative and effective practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent knowledge of good working practices within safeguarding, dignity in care and infection control are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has a supportive approach to staff development including internal transfer periods and rotational posts. We are committed to staff development and training and offer an exceptional Clinical Education package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All interested Nurses are invited to apply and shortlisted candidates will be invited to a closed interview day next month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kerrie Linger kerrie.linger@ulh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
